1
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:13,820
When are you going to divorce him?

2
00:02:13,880 --> 00:02:14,880
Wait a bit longer.

3
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:17,800
Yanzi.

4
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,460
When did he hit you?

5
00:02:20,480 --> 00:02:21,740
The night before last.

6
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:24,770
He complained I took too long to open the door.

7
00:02:31,079 --> 00:02:33,140
What took you so long to open the door?

8
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,360
Come here.

9
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,480
Come here.

10
00:02:37,680 --> 00:02:39,280
What were you doing in there?

11
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:41,680
Who told you to leave?

12
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,700
Are you cheating on me?

13
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,320
Are you cheating on me?

14
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,600
Tian Liang.

15
00:02:49,880 --> 00:02:51,680
I'm going to kill you.

16
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,490
Alright.

17
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,380
Anyway, days like this

18
00:02:59,680 --> 00:03:00,680
will be over soon.

19
00:03:02,080 --> 00:03:02,680
Yanzi.

20
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:05,840
Trust me.

21
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:08,800
I will treat you well from now on.

22
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:36,579
Master.

23
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:38,329
Come.

24
00:03:39,360 --> 00:03:42,160
The crime scene is by the river at the foot of Dahei Mountain.

25
00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:43,820
The report was made at 1:35 PM.

26
00:03:44,079 --> 00:03:45,320
The informants are a man and a woman.

27
00:03:45,320 --> 00:03:46,840
The man is Li Wei, and the woman is Zhang Yan.

28
00:03:46,840 --> 00:03:48,840
Their relationship is currently undetermined.

29
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,800
Our colleagues from the forensics department

30
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:51,000
are finishing up the scene investigation.

31
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:51,800
They will be done soon.

32
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:52,840
Once they're done, we can enter the scene.

33
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,120
Hello, Captain Jiang.

34
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:53,920
Zhao is currently with the informants

35
00:03:53,920 --> 00:03:55,040
getting the specific details.

36
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,320
What should we do next, Master?

37
00:03:56,320 --> 00:03:57,160
We were just waiting for you.

38
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,760
Zhao, Captain Jiang is here.

39
00:03:59,040 --> 00:03:59,880
Captain Jiang.

40
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:01,540
These two are the informants.

41
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:05,920
Hello.

42
00:04:06,480 --> 00:04:07,440
I am Jiang Mei.

43
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,740
Who found the severed arm?

44
00:04:25,360 --> 00:04:26,490
When did you find it?

45
00:04:27,040 --> 00:04:28,520
I don't remember the exact time.

46
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:29,480
We were by that rock

47
00:04:29,480 --> 00:04:30,680
when we were resting.

48
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,200
We found it in the water by accident.

49
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:34,560
After you found it,

50
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:36,290
did you report it immediately?

51
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:37,920
After a while.

52
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:39,600
Why?

53
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,520
We were mostly scared at the time,

54
00:04:42,520 --> 00:04:44,200
afraid of being treated as suspects.

55
00:04:44,200 --> 00:04:46,000
After you found the severed arm,

56
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,930
did you notice anyone around here?

57
00:04:48,600 --> 00:04:49,600
We were too scared

58
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:50,940
and didn't notice.

59
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:51,880
No.

60
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:03,810
Chief Wu.

61
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,050
How is the scene?

62
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:07,400
Only a severed arm was found at the scene.

63
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:09,460
We are still investigating the rest.

64
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,220
Do you need people to help?

65
00:05:11,360 --> 00:05:11,840
No need.

66
00:05:12,560 --> 00:05:14,160
Report the situation in a timely manner.

67
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:14,640
Yes.

68
00:05:16,080 --> 00:05:16,600
Master.

69
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,960
We've investigated the surrounding 200 meters.

70
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,490
No useful clues were found.

71
00:05:20,640 --> 00:05:22,400
Besides, it rained heavily last night,

72
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:23,860
washing everything away.

73
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,960
Then mark the scene well,

74
00:05:26,240 --> 00:05:27,570
expand the search area,

75
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:29,800
and try to find useful clues as soon as possible.

76
00:05:29,800 --> 00:05:30,320
Okay.

77
00:05:31,320 --> 00:05:31,780
Master.

78
00:05:32,240 --> 00:05:33,640
There are wild wolves around here.

79
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:34,600
Do you think a wolf

80
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,880
brought the arm here?

81
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:39,440
It would be great if it was a wild wolf.

82
00:05:39,440 --> 00:05:40,120
Why?

83
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,400
So it could take your brain away too.

84
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,240
Go.

85
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:50,560
Think carefully.

86
00:05:50,560 --> 00:05:52,159
Is there anything else you haven't told us?

87
00:05:52,159 --> 00:05:53,640
I've said everything I should.

88
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,680
Did Zhao write it all down?

89
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,540
I wrote it down.

90
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:00,480
At 1:35 PM today,

91
00:06:00,800 --> 00:06:02,080
at the cliff of Dahei Mountain,

92
00:06:02,080 --> 00:06:04,080
a mutilated, severed arm was found.

93
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,400
The arm was cut off from the elbow joint.

94
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,360
It has been sent to the forensics department for examination.

95
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,820
There are no signs of a struggle at the scene.

96
00:06:11,840 --> 00:06:13,400
The soil hasn't been disturbed.

97
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:14,260
We can conclude

98
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,480
that it's neither the primary crime scene

99
00:06:16,480 --> 00:06:17,610
nor the burial site.

100
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,900
If the owner of the severed arm

101
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:21,530
has already been murdered,

102
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,320
around the crime scene,

103
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,960
we haven't found any useful physical evidence yet.

104
00:06:25,960 --> 00:06:29,040
Are there any reports of missing persons?

105
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:31,500
We are currently verifying this.

106
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:35,280
Who are the people

107
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,130
who reported this case?

108
00:06:37,280 --> 00:06:39,210
The reporters are a man and a woman.

109
00:06:39,320 --> 00:06:41,280
Their relationship cannot be confirmed right now,

110
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:42,210
but it feels like

111
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,280
they are more than just acquaintances.

112
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:45,740
Are there any other clues?

113
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:51,490
Not far from the severed arm is a cliff.

114
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:53,000
We suspect the killer

115
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:54,640
threw the body into the river.

116
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,440
How do you plan

117
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:57,400
to approach this?

118
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,480
I suggest

119
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:00,960
we organize a salvage operation

120
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,720
to rule out any suspicions underwater first.

121
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,280
We will continue to investigate the scene

122
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,880
and look for relevant clues.

123
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:26,960
Come down quickly!

124
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,000
Don't jump!

125
00:07:28,280 --> 00:07:29,200
Come down.

126
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,360
Ms. Xia.

127
00:07:33,520 --> 00:07:35,720
What's wrong? Are you not feeling well?

128
00:07:36,080 --> 00:07:36,560
No.

129
00:07:36,920 --> 00:07:38,760
I just didn't sleep well yesterday.

130
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:40,560
Did you fight with your husband?

131
00:07:41,520 --> 00:07:43,000
I haven't even seen him lately.

132
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:44,440
I couldn't fight with him even if I wanted to.

133
00:07:44,440 --> 00:07:46,240
Well, your husband is so handsome

134
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,300
and so successful.

135
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,880
That's why they say a plain husband is a treasure.

136
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,000
I didn't get it before.

137
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:53,600
Now I do, but it's too late.

138
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:54,680
You're so funny.

139
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:57,330
The saying goes, 'A plain wife is a treasure.'

140
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:58,760
Isn't the logic the same?

141
00:07:59,080 --> 00:08:00,800
If you could choose again,

142
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,160
would you pick an ugly,

143
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,160
unsuccessful man

144
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,960
who relies on you to support him?

145
00:08:04,960 --> 00:08:05,880
Oh no!

146
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:09,520
There's a student on the roof of Academic Building 1

147
00:08:09,520 --> 00:08:12,120
threatening to jump. We've called the police.

148
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:14,480
Sir,

149
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:15,720
please open the gate for me.

150
00:08:15,720 --> 00:08:16,880
I'm a student's family member.

151
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:18,040
Which student?

152
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:18,840
If you keep dawdling,

153
00:08:18,840 --> 00:08:19,840
the student will jump. Thank you, sir.

154
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:20,880
Who are you?

155
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,520
Don't come closer!

156
00:08:21,520 --> 00:08:21,920
Okay.

157
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,160
Okay, I won't come closer.

158
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:23,760
I won't.

159
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,050
Calm down, okay?

160
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:25,960
I'm Xia Lin,

161
00:08:26,120 --> 00:08:27,360
a teacher at our school.

162
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,360
Whatever problem you have,

163
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,620
I can help you solve it.

164
00:08:30,840 --> 00:08:31,400
Trust me.

165
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:32,960
You must be lying to me.

166
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,159
Why would I lie to you?

167
00:08:34,320 --> 00:08:35,440
Since I came up here,

168
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:37,400
I'm here to help you solve your problem.

169
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,400
It's all my dad's fault.

170
00:08:38,400 --> 00:08:39,860
He's seeing someone else.

171
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,530
My mom will never come back.

172
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,440
I understand how you feel,

173
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:45,020
but let me tell you,

174
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:45,760
doing this now

175
00:08:45,760 --> 00:08:47,020
won't solve anything.

176
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,720
If he insists on being with that woman...

177
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:49,400
I will jump down.

178
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:49,730
Okay.

179
00:08:49,960 --> 00:08:50,620
No problem.

180
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,080
I will contact your father,

181
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:52,480
okay?

182
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:53,760
Come, calm down.

183
00:08:53,760 --> 00:08:54,600
Give me your hand.

184
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,240
I promise you.

185
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,170
I will help you find your dad, okay?

186
00:09:01,080 --> 00:09:02,320
You must be lying to me.

187
00:09:02,320 --> 00:09:03,520
I won't lie to you.

188
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:04,640
Trust me.

189
00:09:05,120 --> 00:09:05,650
Trust me.

190
00:09:06,840 --> 00:09:08,320
Okay, okay.

191
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:11,890
Alright.

192
00:09:12,320 --> 00:09:13,280
The student is safe now.

193
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:14,010
Don't worry.

194
00:09:14,320 --> 00:09:15,250
Go back to class.

195
00:09:15,800 --> 00:09:16,240
Okay.

196
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:16,840
Thank you.

197
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,640
However, facing our camera,

198
00:09:42,640 --> 00:09:44,700
Director Xia refused the interview.

199
00:09:49,920 --> 00:09:51,580
Am I prettier, or is your wife?

200
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:54,080
You little minx.

201
00:10:00,640 --> 00:10:01,970
All right. I won't look.

202
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:04,760
Let me ask you.

203
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:07,580
I heard the Xijiao project is having a hard time.

204
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:10,000
Xincheng does have connections at the top.

205
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:10,640
But...

206
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:12,640
But what?

207
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:14,480
You have me.

208
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,100
Come in.

209
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:22,920
Lao Jin.

210
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:25,720
How is it?

211
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:30,240
Can you determine the approximate time of death?

212
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,800
Normally, yes.

213
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,720
But this severed arm has been soaking in water for too long,

214
00:10:34,720 --> 00:10:37,080
and the level of decomposition is too high.

215
00:10:37,080 --> 00:10:38,810
Just give me an estimated time.

216
00:10:39,720 --> 00:10:41,080
Can you confirm it's a male?

217
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,320
Yes, I can confirm that.

218
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:42,760
Okay.

219
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,040
Contact me as soon as you have any news.

220
00:10:45,040 --> 00:10:46,080
All right, don't worry.

221
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,040
Thanks for your help, Mr. Jin.

222
00:10:47,040 --> 00:10:47,770
I'm leaving.

223
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:53,300
When the incident happened at school the other day,

224
00:10:53,800 --> 00:10:54,960
I saw you.

225
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,410
You've got some good moves.

226
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:02,210
It was still a struggle.

227
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:22,140
That matter I talked to you about,

228
00:11:22,160 --> 00:11:23,560
have you thought it over?

229
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:25,850
Chief Wu, I think

230
00:11:26,480 --> 00:11:27,800
let's just forget about it.

231
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:28,800
I have already...

232
00:11:31,520 --> 00:11:32,000
Come.

233
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:36,690
How is it?

234
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,880
Within a one-kilometer radius of the crime scene,

235
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,480
no other body parts were found.

236
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:42,480
We have already started salvaging.

237
00:11:42,600 --> 00:11:44,260
Are you having difficulties?

238
00:11:45,280 --> 00:11:46,540
It will take some time.

239
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:49,240
I am transferring someone to your team.

240
00:11:49,240 --> 00:11:49,800
Who?

241
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:50,800
Shen Feng.

242
00:11:51,360 --> 00:11:52,290
Which Shen Feng?

243
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,800
The unmanageable one.

244
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:00,360
Isn't he doing desk work now?

245
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,560
He is an experienced detective.

246
00:12:02,680 --> 00:12:04,600
He still has the capability.

247
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:06,280
No matter how capable he is,

248
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:07,360
he's been doing desk work for too long.

249
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,160
He'll be out of breath after running two steps. Working on the front line,

250
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,680
is definitely not going to work, Chief Wu.

251
00:12:10,680 --> 00:12:12,800
Aren't we also doing desk work?

252
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,040
It's settled.

253
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,200
No, Chief Wu.

254
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:15,890
Chief Wu.

255
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:19,560
About what you just mentioned,

256
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,760
it's not impossible.

257
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:21,640
Okay.

258
00:12:23,040 --> 00:12:24,100
It's settled then.

259
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,960
I'll leave the paperwork to you.

260
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:28,220
Thank you for the opportunity, Chief Wu.

261
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,740
Hello, Captain Jiang.

262
00:12:29,920 --> 00:12:30,650
I don't pant.

263
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,400
Hello.

264
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:39,560
You don't.

265
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:42,320
Chief Wu.

266
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:49,360
I will report for duty tomorrow.

267
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:54,560
Mentor,

268
00:12:55,160 --> 00:12:55,820
who is that?

269
00:12:56,240 --> 00:12:57,770
He's here to cause trouble.

270
00:13:00,160 --> 00:13:01,160
Whether this case

271
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:02,440
is an impulsive crime

272
00:13:02,920 --> 00:13:04,160
or malicious dismemberment,

273
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,360
we must find out ASAP.

274
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:08,560
Based on the footprints extracted from the scene,

275
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:09,620
we can confirm that

276
00:13:09,760 --> 00:13:12,160
there were only two people who reported it.

277
00:13:12,720 --> 00:13:14,450
Organize a salvage operation.

278
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,880
Searched for a long time.

279
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,160
What did they pull up?

280
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:33,160
You've been thinking for a while.

281
00:13:33,160 --> 00:13:34,560
What did you come up with?

282
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:39,460
Hello, Lao Jin.

283
00:13:39,680 --> 00:13:41,520
Captain Jiang, the results are out.
